<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:10.2%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Item&#160;7.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	MANAGEMENT&#8217;S DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS OF FINANCIAL CONDITION AND RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;, &#8220;we&#8221;, &#8220;us&#8221; or &#8220;our&#8221;) reports two distinct business segments, Hub and Mode. The Mode segment includes only the business we acquired on April&#160;1, 2011. The Hub segment includes all businesses other than Mode. Hub Group refers to the consolidated results for the company, including both the Mode and Hub segments. For the segment financial results, refer to Note 5 to the consolidated financial statements.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We are one of the largest intermodal marketing companies (&#8220;IMC&#8221;) in the United States and a full service transportation provider offering intermodal, truck brokerage and logistics services. We operate through a nationwide network of operating centers and independent business owners.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We also arrange for the transportation of freight by truck, providing customers with another option for their transportation needs. We match the customers&#8217; needs with carriers&#8217; capacity to provide the most effective service and price combinations. As part of our truck brokerage services, we negotiate rates, track shipments in transit and handle claims for freight loss or damage on behalf of our customers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our logistics service consists of complex transportation management services, including load consolidation, mode optimization and carrier management. These service offerings are designed to take advantage of the increasing trend for shippers to outsource all or a greater portion of their transportation needs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub has full time marketing representatives throughout North America who service local, regional and national accounts. We believe that fostering long-term customer relationships is critical to our success and allows us to better understand our customers&#8217; needs and specifically tailor our transportation services to them.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub&#8217;s account management group works with pricing and operations to enhance Hub&#8217;s customer margins. We are working on margin enhancement projects including using the most cost effective drayage carriers, improving utilization, improving our accessorial management, reducing empty miles and routinely reviewing and improving low margin loads.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	17
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage19"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU19">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub&#8217;s top 50 customers represent approximately 64% of the Hub segment revenue for the ye
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ar ended December&#160;31, 2016. We use various performance indicators to manage our business. We closely monitor margin and gains and losses for our top 50 customers. We also evaluate on-time performance, cost per load and daily sales outstanding by customer a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ccount. Vendor cost changes and vendor service issues are also monitored closely.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode has approximately 182 agents, consisting of 102 sales/operating agents, known as Independent Business Owners (&#8220;IBOs&#8221;), who sell and operate the business throughout North America and 80 sales only agents. Mode also has a temperature protected services division operated out of our Oak Brook, IL headquarters and corporate offices in Memphis, TN and Dallas, TX. Mode&#8217;s top 20 customers represent approximately 39% of the Mode segment revenue for the year ended December&#160;31, 2016. We closely monitor revenue and margin for these customers. We believe Mode brings us highly complementary service offerings, more scale and a talented sales channel that allows us to better reach small and midsize customers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Revenue
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s revenue increased 1.3% to $3.6 billion in 2016 from $3.5 billion in 2015 due primarily to higher volume across our business lines.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment revenue increased 2.1% to $2.7 billion. Hub segment intermodal revenue was flat at $1.8 billion. Intermodal volume increased 2% and price and mix combined were also up.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were offset by a decline in fuel revenue. Hub segment truck brokerage revenue increased 10% to $392 million. Truck brokerage handled 14% more loads, but fuel, mix and price combined were down 4%.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hub segment logistics revenue increased 5% to $557 million related primarily to growth with new customers.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s revenue increased 2.2% to $948.7 million in 2016 from $928.7 million in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mode&#8217;s intermodal revenue increased 1% primarily due to a 2% increase in volume which was partially offset by a decline in fuel revenue. Mode&#8217;s truck brokerage revenue decreased 2% and Mode&#8217;s logistics revenue increased 18%.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	18
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Transportation Costs
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s transportation costs remained consistent at $3.1 billion in both 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Transportation costs in 2016 consisted of purchased transportation costs of $2.8 billion and equipment and driver related costs of $360.8 million compared to 2015 which consisted of purchased transportation costs of $2.7 billion and equipment and driver related costs of $386.4 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a percentage of revenue, transportation costs decreased in 2016 to 87.3% from 88.3% in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment transportation costs remained consistent at $2.4 billion in both 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hub segment transportation costs in 2016 consisted of $2.0 billion in purchased transportation costs, which was consistent with 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equipment and driver related costs decreased 7% to $357.3 million in 2016 from $383.0 million in 2015 due primarily to a decrease in fuel costs and shutting down our Southern California drayage operation in the first quarter of 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Mode segment transportation costs increased 1.7% to $823.5 million in 2016 from $810.1 million in 2015. Mode segment transportation costs are primarily purchased transportation costs which increased due primarily to higher volume in intermodal and truck brokerage.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Gross Margin
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s gross margin increased 10.2% to $454.8 million in 2016 from $412.7 million in 2015. Hub Group&#8217;s gross margin as a percentage of revenue increased to 12.7% in 2016 from 11.7% in 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment gross margin increased 12.1% to $329.6 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Hub&#8217;s $35.5 million gross margin increase resulted from an increase in gross margin in all three business lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Intermodal margin increased due to price increases, a 2% increase in loads, improved accessorial management, lower dray costs and improved mix and lane balance.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rail cost increases partially offset some of this improvement.&nbsp;&nbsp;Truck brokerage margin increased as a result of growth with targeted customer accounts. Logistics margin increased due to providing additional services to existing accounts and growth with new customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a percentage of revenue, Hub segment gross margin increased to 12.1% in 2016 from 11.0% in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
	Intermodal gross margin as a percentage of sales increased 90 basis points because of price increases, lower drayage costs and improved accessorial management. Truck brokerage gross margin as a percentage of sales was up 150 basis points due to more value added services and better purchasing. Logistics gross margin as a percentage of sales was up 120 basis points due to improved customer mix, operational efficiencies and more cost effective purchasing.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s gross margin increased 5.6% to $125.2 million in 2016 from $118.6 million in 2015 due to growth in all three business lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mode&#8217;s gross margin as a percentage of revenue increased to 13.2% in 2016 from 12.8% in 2015 due to a 140 basis point improvement in truck brokerage yield and a 30 basis point improvement in intermodal yield.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	19
</P>

	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Salaries and Benefits
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s salaries and benefits increased&nbsp;&nbsp;to $180.5 million in 2016 from $158.9 million in 2015. As a percentage of revenue, Hub Group&#8217;s salaries and benefits increased to 5.1% in 2016 from 4.5% in 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM_OLE_LINK16">
</A>
	The Hub segment salaries and benefits increase o
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM_OLE_LINK16">
</A>
	f $21.1 million was due primarily to increases of $10.2 million related to higher headcount and merit increases, $6.5 million of employee bonus expense, $1.8 million of commissions, $1.4 million of employee benefits, $0.7 million of payroll taxes and $0.5 million of compensation related to restricted stock awards.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s salaries and benefits expense increased to $15.3 million in 2016 from $14.9 million in 2015.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>
	The increase was due primarily to increases of $0.7 million related to higher headcount and merit increases and $0.1 million of compensation related to restricted stock awards partially offset by a decrease in employee bonus expense of $0.4 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub&#8217;s headcount as of December&#160;31, 2016 and 2015 was 1,657 and 1,480, respectively, which excludes drivers, as driver costs are included in transportation costs. As of December&#160;31, 2016 and 2015, Mode had 127 and 117 employees, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Agent Fees and Commissions
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s agent fees and commissions increased to $72.9 million in 2016 from $68.7 million in 2015. As a percentage of revenue, these expenses remained consistent at 2.0% in both 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase in the expense was primarily related to Mode&#8217;s increase in gross margin.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Mode segment agent fees and commissions expense increase of $4.2 million was primarily due to the increase in gross margin.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	General and Administrative
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s general and administrative expenses increased to $68.6 million in 2016 from $60.0 million in 2015. As a percentage of revenue, these expenses increased to 1.9% in 2016 from 1.7% in 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment increase of $7.8 million was due primarily to increases in IT consulting expenses of $3.8 million, IT maintenance expense of $1.4 million, legal expenses of $1.0 million, office expenses and travel and entertainment of $0.9 million each, recruiting expenses of $0.4 million, general consulting expenses of $0.3 million, rent expense and employee training of $0.2 million each and equipment leases of $0.1 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were partially offset by more gains on the sale of fixed assets of $0.6 million, an intercompany charge to Mode of $0.6 million and a reduction in bad debt expense of $0.2 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU23">
</A>
	Mode&#8217;s general and administrative expenses increased to $7.8 million in 2016 from $7.0 million in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;The increase was primarily due to an intercompany charge from Hub of $0.6 million and repairs and maintenance expenses, fewer gains on the sale of
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	20
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage22"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	fixed assets and consulting services of $0.1 million each.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were partially offset
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	by a decrease in bad debt expense of $0.1 million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Depreciation and Amortization
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s depreciation and amortization increased to $9.0 million in 2016 from $8.0 million in 2015. This expense as a percentage of revenue remained consistent at 0.2% in both 2016 and 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment&#8217;s depreciation expense increased to $7.7 million in 2016 from $6.7 million in 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;This increase was related primarily to more depreciation related to additional computer software.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s depreciation expense remained consistent at $1.3 million in 2016 and 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Other Income (Expense)
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s other expense decreased to $2.4 million in 2016 from $5.4 million in 2015 due primarily to gains on foreign currency translation of $0.8 million in 2016 compared to losses of $2.6 million in 2015, partially offset by increases of $0.7 million in interest expense in 2016 related to our tractor and container debt.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Provision for Income Taxes
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The provision for income taxes increased to $46.6 million in 2016 from $40.6 million in 2015 due primarily to an increase in our pretax income and to a lesser extent an increase in our effective tax rate.&#160; Our effective tax rate was 38.4% in 2016 and 36.4% in 2015.&#160; The 2016 effective tax rate increased primarily due to the effects of income tax law changes enacted by the state of Connecticut in 2016 which raised our 2016 rate and income tax law changes enacted by the state of Missouri in 2015 which lowered our 2015 rate.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net Income
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net income increased to $74.8 million in 2016 from $70.9 million in 2015 due primarily to increased margin, partially offset by higher operating expenses and higher income tax expense.
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Revenue
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s revenue decreased 1.3% to $3.5 billion in 2015 from $3.6 billion in 2014 due primarily to lower fuel revenue.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment revenue decreased 1.6% to $2.7 billion. Hub segment intermodal revenue was flat at $1.8 billion. Intermodal volume increased 3% and price and mix combined were also up.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were offset by a decline in fuel revenue. Hub segment truck brokerage revenue increased 5% to $355 million. Truck brokerage handled 11% more loads, but fuel, mix and price combined were down.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hub segment logistics revenue decreased 6% to $532 million due to losing one customer in May of 2015 and one customer selling a portion of its business and taking another portion of its business in house.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s revenue decreased 0.3% to $928.7 million in 2015 from $931.1 million in 2014. Mode&#8217;s intermodal revenue increased 4% primarily due to an 8% increase in volume which was partially offset by a decline in fuel revenue. Mode&#8217;s truck brokerage revenue decreased 6% primarily due to a decrease in revenue per load that was driven by lower fuel revenue.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mode&#8217;s logistics revenue increased 1%.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	21
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	-
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;WIDTH:1%; BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE 2.5PT TRANSPARENT;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%; BORDER-TOP:SOLID 0.75PT #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE 2.5PT #000000;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	$
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:7.76%; BORDER-TOP:SOLID 0.75PT #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE 2.5PT #000000;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	83,877
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;WIDTH:1%; BORDER-BOTTOM:DOUBLE 2.5PT TRANSPARENT;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:1PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:8PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Transportation Costs
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s transportation costs decreased 2.7% to $3.1 billion in 2015 from $3.2 billion in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Transportation costs in 2015 consisted of purchased transportation costs of $2.7 billion and equipment and driver related costs of $386.4 million compared to 2014 costs of purchased transportation of $2.8 billion and equipment and driver related costs of $425.9 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a percentage of revenue, transportation costs decreased in 2015 to 88.3% from 89.6% in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment transportation costs decreased 3.1% to $2.4 billion in 2015 from $2.5 billion in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Hub segment transportation costs in 2015 consisted of $2.0 billion in purchased transportation costs, which was consistent with 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equipment and driver related costs decreased 9% to $383.0 million in 2015 from $421.7 million in 2014 due primarily to a decrease in fuel cost and a decrease in driver count.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Mode segment transportation costs decreased 1.5% to $810.1 million in 2015 from $822.4 million in 2014. Mode segment transportation costs are primarily purchased transportation costs which decreased due primarily to lower fuel costs, partially offset by higher volume in intermodal and truck brokerage.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Gross Margin
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s gross margin increased 11.4% to $412.7 million in 2015 from $370.4 million in 2014. Hub Group&#8217;s gross margin as a percentage of revenue increased to 11.7% in 2015 from 10.4% in 2014.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment gross margin increased 12.4% to $294.1 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	Hub&#8217;s $32.5 million gross margin increase resulted from an increase in gross margin in all three business lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Intermodal margin increased due to price increases, a 3% increase in loads and a more favorable mix.&nbsp;&nbsp;Truck brokerage margin increased as a result of growth with targeted customer accounts. Logistics margin increased due to providing additional services to existing accounts and growth with new customers.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a percentage of revenue, Hub segment gross margin increased to 11.0% in 2015 from 9.6% in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
	Intermodal gross margin as a percentage of sales increased 130 basis points because of price increases, lower drayage costs, improved accessorial management and effectively using our new load acceptance optimization tool. Truck brokerage gross margin as a percentage of sales was up 200 basis points due to more value added services, price increases and better purchasing. Logistics gross margin as a percentage of sales was up 110 basis points due to purchasing more cost effectively, price increases and changes in customer mix.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s gross margin increased 9.0% to $118.6 million in 2015 from $108.8 million in 2014 due to growth in all three business lines.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mode&#8217;s gross margin as a percentage of revenue increased to 12.8% in 2015 from 11.7% in 2014 due primarily to a 110 basis point improvement in intermodal yield and a 120 basis point improvement in truck brokerage yield. Mode&#8217;s logistics gross margin increased by 100 basis points.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	22
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:18.16%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:9PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.4
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PT;PADDING-RIGHT:0.75PT;PADDING-TOP:0.75PT;PADDING-BOTTOM:0PT;WIDTH:1%;WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:1PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#160;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:8PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Salaries and Benefits
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s salaries and benefits increased to $158.9 million in 2015 from $136.5 million in 2014. As a percentage of revenue, Hub Group&#8217;s salaries and benefits increased to 4.5% in 2015 from 3.8% in 2014.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment salaries and benefits increase of $21.9 million was due primarily to increases in employee bonuses of $11.2 million, salaries of $6.9 million, payroll taxes and commissions of $1.5 million each, severance of $0.9 million and employee benefits of $0.6 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were partially offset by a decrease in compensation related to restricted stock awards of $0.7 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s salaries and benefits expense increased to $14.9 million in 2015 from $14.4 million in 2014.
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>
	The increase was due primarily to increases in bonuses of $0.5 million and compensation related to restricted stock awards of $0.2 million partially offset by decreases in salaries expense and employee benefits expense of $0.1 million each.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub&#8217;s headcount as of December&#160;31, 2015 and 2014 was 1,480 and 1,380, respectively, which excludes drivers, as driver costs are included in transportation costs. As of December&#160;31, 2015 and 2014, Mode had 117 and 125 employees, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Agent Fees and Commissions
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s agent fees and commissions increased to $68.7 million in 2015 from $62.0 million in 2014. As a percentage of revenue, these expenses increased to 2.0% in 2015 from 1.8% in 2014. The increase in the expense and the increase in the percentage of revenue were primarily related to Mode&#8217;s increase in gross margin.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Mode segment agent fees and commissions expense increase of $6.7 million was primarily due to the increase in gross margin.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	General and Administrative
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s general and administrative expenses increased to $60.0 million in 2015 from $58.0 million in 2014. As a percentage of revenue, these expenses increased to 1.7% in 2015 from 1.6% in 2014.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment increase of $1.9 million was due primarily to increases in personal property and real estate taxes and repairs and maintenance expense of $0.8 million each, technology communication charges of $0.6 million, bad debt expense of $0.2 million and an increase in the loss on the sale of fixed assets of $0.1 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were partially offset by decreases in training expense and temporary employee expense of $0.2 million each as well as general insurance and rent expense of $0.1 million each.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	23
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage25"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU26">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s general and administrative expenses increased to $7.0 million in 2015 from $6.9 mil
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	lion in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The increase was primarily due to an increase outside services of $0.2 million partially offset by a decrease in repairs and maintenance expense of $0.1 million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Depreciation and Amortization
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s depreciation and amortization increased to $8.0 million in 2015 from $7.8 million in 2014. This expense as a percentage of revenue remained constant at 0.2% in both 2015 and 2014.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Hub segment&#8217;s depreciation expense increased to $6.7 million in 2015 from $6.2 million in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;This increase was related primarily to more depreciation related to additional computer hardware and software.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Mode&#8217;s depreciation expense decreased to $1.3 million in 2015 from $1.6 million in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp; The decrease in expense was primarily related to
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	less depreciation related to computer
</FONT>
	hardware and software.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Driver Settlements and Related Costs
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In 2014, the Hub segment recorded a charge of $10.3 million for driver settlements and related costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This charge included $9.3 million in settlements for individual drivers and $1.0 million of related legal, communication and implementation costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;This expense as a percentage of revenue was 0.3% in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2015, there were no such costs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Impairment of Software
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:3.33%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In 2014, the Hub segment recorded a charge of $11.9 million related to the write-off of software development costs as a result of our decision to terminate a long-term technology project.&nbsp;&nbsp;This expense as a percentage of revenue was 0.3% in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2015, there were no such costs.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Other Income (Expense)
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Hub Group&#8217;s other expense increased to $5.4 million in 2015 from $2.0 million in 2014 due primarily to $1.2 million in increased interest expense related to our tractor and container debt as well as an increase of $2.3 million in foreign currency translation losses.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Provision for Income Taxes
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The provision for income taxes increased to $40.6 million in 2015 from $30.3 million in 2014 primarily due to the increase in our pretax income.&#160; Our effective tax rate was 36.4% in 2015 and 37.0% in 2014.&#160; The rate decrease was primarily due to the effect of state tax apportionment changes reducing our provision for state taxes.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net Income
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net income increased to $70.9 million in 2015 from $51.6 million in 2014 due primarily to increased margin, partially offset by higher operating expenses and higher income tax expense.
</P>
</EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<EFX_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL>
<A NAME="FIS_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:18PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	LIQUIDITY AND CAPITAL RESOURCES
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	During 2016, we funded operations, capital expenditures, capital leases, purchase of treasury stock, repayments of debt and stock buy backs related to employee withholding upon vesting of restricted stock through cash flows from operations, proceeds from the issuance of long-term debt and cash on hand. We believe that our cash, cash flow from operations and borrowings available under our Credit Agreement will be sufficient to meet our cash needs for at least the next twelve months.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Cash provided by operating activities for the year ended December&#160;31, 2016 was approximately $102.5 million, which resulted primarily from income of $74.8 million plus the adjustment for non-cash charges of $65.7 million less the change in operating assets and liabilities of $38.0 million. The $69.2 million decrease in cash flow provided by operating activities for 2016 compared to 2015 was primarily attributed to a negative cash change in operating assets and liabilities of $77.7 million offset by an increase in non-cash charges of $4.6 million and net income of $3.9 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;The negative cash change in assets and liabilities in 2016 versus 2015 resulted from higher Days Sales Outstanding (&#8220;DSO&#8221;) in 2016 versus 2015 caused by extended terms by select customers, partially offset by slower payments to our vendors.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	24
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage26"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="HUBG-10K_20161231_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU27">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Cash provided by operating activities was approximately $171.7 million and $98.5 million for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The cash provided by operating activities in 2015 resulted primarily from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	income of $70.9 million adjusted for non-cash charges of $61.1 million and the change in operating assets and liabilities of $39.7 million. The $73.2 million increase in cash flow provided by operating activities for 2015 compared to 2014 was primarily att
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ributed to a positive cash change in operating assets and liabilities of $66.7 million and an increase in net income of $19.4 million, partially offset by a decrease in non-cash charges of $12.9 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;The positive cash change in assets and liabilities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	in 2015 versus 2014 resulted from an improvement in DSO and the use of prepaid for taxes, partially offset by quicker payments to our vendors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net cash used in investing activities for the year ended December&#160;31, 2016 was $105.3 million which includes proceeds from the sale of equipment of $2.1 million. Capital expenditures of $107.4 million included containers of $59 million, land of $15 million, technology projects of $13 million, purchases of other transportation equipment of $12 million, tractor purchases of $6 million and leasehold improvements of $2 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Capital expenditures increased by approximately $24.4 million in 2016 as compared to 2015. The 2016 increase was due to increases in container purchases of $39 million, land of $15 million, technology of $7 million and leasehold improvements of $2 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;These increases were partially offset by approximately $39 million more of tractor purchases in 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net cash used in investing activities for the year ended December 31, 2015 was $80.7 million as compared to $118.6 million in 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;Capital expenditures decreased by approximately $36.1 million in 2015 as compared to 2014.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 2015 decrease was due to decreases in container purchases of $18 million, tractor purchases of $14 million, payments for our new headquarters in Oak Brook of $8 million and technology and other purchases of $3 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;These decreases were partially offset by approximately $7 million more of transportation equipment purchased in 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In 2017, we estimate capital expenditures will range from $155 million to $165 million. We have ordered 4,000 containers and plan to retire 800 containers for a net add of 3,200 containers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect to purchase between 100 and 150 tractors, expand our corporate headquarters and invest in technology projects.&nbsp;&nbsp;We have not decided if we will finance our equipment purchases using leases or debt.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net cash used in financing activities for the year ended December 31, 2016 was $77.4 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;We used $100.0 million to purchase treasury stock, $34.8 million for repayment of long-term debt, $2.6 million for capital lease payments and $2.5 million of cash for stock tendered for payments of withholding taxes. These payments were partially offset by proceeds from the issuance of debt of $62.2 million and excess tax benefits from share-based compensation of $0.4 million as a financing cash in-flow.&nbsp;&nbsp;The $84.5 million increase in cash used in financing activities for 2016 compared to 2015 was primarily due to the increase in treasury stock purchases of $71.2 million, an increase in debt payments of $11.6 million and a decrease in the proceeds from issuance of debt of $2.3 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Net cash provided by financing activities for the year ended December 31, 2015 was $7.1 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;We used $28.8 million to purchase treasury stock, $23.2 million for repayment of long-term debt, $2.9 million of cash for stock tendered for payments of withholding taxes and $2.5 million for capital lease payments. These payments were offset by proceeds from the issuance of debt of $64.4 million and excess tax benefits from share-based compensation of $0.2 million as a financing cash in-flow.&nbsp;&nbsp;The $53.7 million decrease in cash provided by financing activities for 2015 compared to 2014 was primarily due to the decrease of $26.7 million in debt issuance, additional debt payments of $16.0 million and additional treasury stock purchases of $10.8 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.5%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Cash paid for income taxes of $33.2 million was less than our income tax expense of $46.6 million primarily due to favorable timing differences between our tax returns and financial statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;The largest favorable timing difference in 2016 related to depreciation for tractors and containers. In 2017, if we finance our equipment purchases with debt, we expect our cash paid for taxes to be less than our income tax expense because we expect to have a favorable timing difference between the 2017 tax return and financial statements related to depreciation for tractors, containers and chassis.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, we are unable to predict the effect federal tax reform, if enacted and effective in 2017, would have on our 2017 effective tax rate.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	See Note 10 of the consolidated financial statements for details related to interest rates and commitment fees.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We have standby letters of credit that expire in 2017. As of December&#160;31, 2016, our letters of credit were $11.8 million.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:2.27%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Our unused and available borrowings under our bank revolving line of credit were $38.2 million as of December&#160;31, 2016 and $41.8 million as of December&#160;31, 2015. We believe our line of credit is adequate to meet our cash needs.&nbsp;&nbsp;We were in compliance with our debt covenants as of December&#160;31, 2016.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	25
</P>

	In addition to the commitments above, in November 2016, we committed to acquire 4,000 53&#8217; containers.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect the total purchase price of these containers to be approximately $40 million.&nbsp;&nbsp;We expect to take delivery of the equipment between February and November of 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are evaluating whether we finance the containers with a lease or debt.
